                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="E.11.m">
                            <title>Tripādapaṃcakaśānti</title>
                            <incipit><locus>F.1 </locus>śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ || brahmapurāṇe
                                tripādapaṃcakaśāṃtir ucyate cha || brahmovāca | sūtikāṃte yathā
                                vipraiḥ śāṃtiṃ kuryād yathāvidhi | anyathā na gatiṃ prāye
                                pretaputreṣu no śubhaṃ |</incipit>
                            <explicit><locus>F.3 </locus>...brāhmaṇabhojanāṃte iṣṭaiḥ saha bhuṃjīte
                                || iti tripādaśāṃtiḥ || alakṣmīr yac ca dauṣṭyaṃ me sarvagātreṣv
                                avasthitaṃ || tat sarvaṃ praśamaṃ yātu lakṣmīṃ puṣṭiṃ ca varddhaya
                                || saṃvat 1877 aṣāḍhe māse</explicit>
                            <note>On <locus>F.3v</locus>, a second hand has written: ||
                                tripādaśāṃtisāmagrī || jalapātra | kaṃku | ...mṛttikā |
                                choḍiyā</note>
                        </msItem>

